The need for speed The Run is fighting all over America.
Revision
Originally a problem-free race is transformed by a set of stupid mistakes of people who have nothing to do with it in a routine morning trip to work.
It fulfills everyone’s ambitions to some extent, but it is useless if no one wants to do anything more.
The new subtitled part The Run produced high expectations before its release.
He promised to take a new direction with the already aged Need for Speed racing series and to release a kind of game from the playable parts that would not count only with points.
So we were curious how the passages will be added during which the main hero gets out of his car and does what he wants.
As is already the case in the NFS series, the result is completely different than expected.
These are potentially arcade racing games but the whole is pulling down because of some unnecessary mistakes that have already existed for several years.
These are not really mistakes but rather the expression of a laziness incomprehensible on the part of the developers.
The adventure starts very well.
You are caught up in an adventure whose main hero Jack has character problems and to settle them begins to participate in illegal races across America.
You sit behind the wheel on the west coast in San Francisco and your mission is to arrive first in New York.
The idea has interesting elements.
The itinerary is divided into ten stages and then more than 50 races.
The result is that each race takes place on a different route and the stages planned in different environments that stand out quite well from each other and are interesting.
The player does not have the feeling for a single moment that the game offers him something identical.
Some environments are also pretty, even though the graphical technical level is of the same type as the previous series.
This is not the end of the world.
But driving through the desert, in autumn landscapes or in high snowy mountains is very visually pleasing.
The trials are also occasionally adorned with an atypical element.
For example, in the desert you find yourself in a sandstorm that significantly diminishes your visibility.
Then in the mountains you have to be careful that an avalanche does not fall on you.
In addition to this, the different races are well arranged behind each other.
There are only a few, but that is enough.
There are moments when you try to exceed the required number of opponents (as in a classic race) then you race against the clock (classic dual with the stopwatch) and then still awaits you another duel with an opponent.
From time to time you also have the police who enter the game and try to make the situation difficult for you.
The novelty is the off-vehicle passages.
Rather, it’s an interactive animation when most of the time Jack runs away from someone and you have to help them by tapping the right button at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
What is surprising is that there are fewer moments of this type than you expect (to be concrete there are only three).
The result is quite like this because this element does not risk hindering and places itself, in the context described above, in the elements that decorate the game.
The driving model is in the tradition of previous games.
Which means that there is currently nothing extraordinary but it cannot be said to be negative.
As far as realistic simulation is concerned, you will have to go elsewhere.
But although one can find better in the competition the driving model goes very well with the type of design of the races.
So everything is ok.
Problems begin to appear after a while.
As the driving model differs, that of collisions is not yet at the point.
We do not expect complicated deformation and collisions from this game, but when you do not have, during a collision with any object, the slightest idea of how your car behaves, so it is not completely good.
During tight overtakings you sometimes touch each other slightly, but otherwise your self-departure in crazy jolts.
Or it can be found in crumbs.
Thanks to the reboot system this is not really a problem but it really annoys you.
The reboot is done so that when you have broken your figure or you have gone out in the decor the game brings you back to the moment of the last point on the itinerary.
But you only have 5 restarts.
When you have used all 5 restarts you must start the game again from the beginning.
So it's more of a tool, in case something doesn't go as it should, than something you can really rely on.
Sometimes restarts do not help and the solution must be found by remembering the piece of itinerary in question.
The big thing about this game is that the same actions end up in the same places.
For example, there are certain turns that you have to go through in a certain way or it will not happen.
Otherwise you meet on a given location "civil" vehicles always in the same configuration as you arrived first, fifth, 5 seconds in advance or a minute late.
What makes you angry are situations when you see the opponent easily passing between two cars coming in the opposite direction and when you arrive, you have to either stand aside and contour them or brake them.
It doesn't matter if you meet him because it's "calculated" in such a way that for the given situation it always comes very close to your nose.
The opponents have other advantages.
During all the time of the game, you arrive in some places, again without worrying about time, and you always have the same opponent that precedes you in the same place.
This irritates the most at the end of the game when you ride on a long bridge in the opposite direction.
The opponent must at all costs pass in front of you.
When it passes in front of you it hides the sight of other vehicles in the opposite direction and you collide a good number of times.
It can be understood that the purpose of this game is to do something captivating and full of adrenaline, but it is clear that you get bored quickly.
And that's a shame because through a simple driving model the game is interesting and places with so much action that you don't have time to follow everything that happens.
And it doesn't matter if it's because of the concept of 50 unique routes, the order of the races is such that there is no chance of getting bored or something else.
The original idea is the change of car during races.
You need to pay attention to gas pumps on routes because you can change cars there however most of the time you have enough.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are ideal for cities, big American cylinders for straight highways and super sports cars with exotic rides on very technical driving for example on lace roads in the mountains.
And the challenge mode, which are races in particular places that you know of adventure, goes very well with the main diet of the story.
You receive not only medals but also experience points that add to your profile that is common to challenges and adventure.
When you reach the highest level of driver, different objects begin to unlock:
It connects online with the Autolog feature that, among other things, compares your results with those of other players and provides you with other features in the community.
One of the hardest moves to understand is the situation of the last race of the adventure.
You arrive with your car in the metro tunnel (it looks like) where you drive in the dark on the tracks (it looks like).
Your speed indicator tells you between 150 and 200 km/h (a priori) and behind you arrives a subway train that sends the car directly to the scrap.
At the editorial board we had a discussion for a few days about whether someone really thought about creating this game or whether the authors really think of us as fools.
The technical part of the game is not extra, but the visual part is generally pleasant and in some cases really great.
The problem is that in more extreme situations, imaging does not hold the level and in some cases tragically.
This especially applies to accidents with a large number of participants when fluid imaging no longer serves you well.
The sound part is good and the track is your choice.
In order to please the greatest number and especially the most young audience a new soundtrack was created in the style "I mix everything", but we can expect that no one will buy the game for the music.
Need for Speed: The Run is really confusing.
If the game didn’t have these stupid mistakes we could say without fear that this is the best NFS production in recent years.
But this game feels like it's not finished.
The fun is really good but prepare yourself for mistakes to hit you in the eyes with the strength of an aerodrome reflector.
The Velvet Students in concert with the choirs of the Charles University
The Festa Academica festival offers for the third time festivities that link the International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical part.
During the festival there are 20 choirs from upper and secondary schools.
The pinnacle of the festival is formed by two concerts organized on November 17.
"Charles University has an important role in this festival."
"Among the choirs there is the Choir of the Faculty of Education and Humanities, in the festival committee sits the rector Vaclav Hampl," says the leader of the organising team Jakub Calou.
The highlight of the festival is the concert of the High School and Secondary Class Choir, which takes place with free admission on 17 November from 2 p.m. in the space located in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
On the program is the composition of the well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Celebration Jazz Mass.
In the evening the concert "Students of velvet" takes place in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady during which the choirs of the higher schools as well as that of the Charles University are performed.
The Festa Academica aims not only to celebrate with dignity the International Students’ Day and to commemorate the 22nd anniversary of the velvet revolution, but also to present to the public choir music of the highest level and to develop the creative cooperation of young people.
The main organiser is the Union of Czech Choirs in cooperation with the Jan Kepler High School.
All the action is under the aegis of Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague and Vaclav Hampl, Rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from 16 to 20 November in Prague and Pardubice.
The program also offers high-level concerts, music meetings, student happenings and other activities.
Interested parties will find all the information on the festival’s internet pages www.festacademica.cz.
Vicenova, Ambassador to the European Union:
Czechs behave like negatives and Eurosceptics
"The Lisbon Treaty has radically eliminated the balance between the institutions"
"I didn't expect such a tough war."
"It will last 5.6 years before the situation calms down and all players get used to their new role," Milena Vicenova began her presentation at the Faculty of Law, the Czech ambassador to the European Union.
When she managed to describe the different EU bodies and their relations in such a comprehensible and visible way, to the point that a large number of lecturers from the Charles University Faculty of Law might envy her, she showed how much she takes her motto "understandable and openly about Europe" very seriously.
Vicenova paid tribute to the work of Herman Van Rompuye, the new permanent President of the European Council.
"From the beginning, critics resonated that he's faded, that he's a round-of-leather, that he can't fill any mission and I have to say that he's breathtaking everyone because he's holding his role to perfection."
"He is a man who can listen to 27 member states, communicate well with them and has a clear vision of the direction to take from Europe."
She explained the new post of the High Representative for Foreign Affairs and Defence Policy as part of an answer to the question: "Who is who in the European Union?" "Which phone number should I call?", so as an important step towards the uniqueness and greater legibility of the EU's policy towards states, such as China or India.
Nobody wants to ban our syrecky (cooked cheese that smells very strong)
Mrs Vicenova also mentioned the agenda that the European Council has lived, lives and will live in the near future.
She called the Czech presidency two years ago a success.
The Czechs resolved the rising financial crisis, the gas crisis, or organised an Eastern Partnership Summit.
It called the fall of the governorate very negative and damaged the image of the Czech Republic.
The Czech representation in the EU is currently very busy.
In the words of the Ambassador, "the activity has been in full swing" not only for the Presidency but also for the financial crisis that continues to be resolved even now.
In addition, the new seventh budget of the Union must be approved, which is becoming very complicated due to the current economic situation.
As it would seem that the budget will be thin and with a view to savings, which branch will take precedence, which countries will be helped the most, the least, everything is to be resolved in the context of future negotiations.
The Ambassador recalled her slogans with which she arrived in Brussels "For an understandable Europe".
“I really don’t like abbreviations, foreign words, jargons that no one understands.
As the citizen must understand it is true that in Brussels no one makes round or twisted pickles, bananas differently large or even that no one has forbidden us to make syrecky.
It wants to make better use of the EU environment and see more Czechs in the European institutions.
A multi-speed Europe is waiting for us
According to the ambassador, the Czechs have a reputation for being Eurosceptics and people who only see things in their negative aspect more than positively.
In addition, she is sorry to see such a small Czech representation in the European institutions.
The fault, she said, stems from several factors, such as the timidity of our candidates, their inability to write a letter of motivation and the Czech side's weak support.
In addition to a successful Czech presidency, she then stressed the strength and cooperation of the Visegrad Group.
Believe me, when the Pole, the Magyar, the Slovak come to me, this Frenchman says to me, ‘Hey, what are you doing there, what is this Visegrad group still doing?’ and he is not at all happy.”
According to Mrs Vicenova, in the near future, the Member States are waiting for tough new rules on fiscal policy.
It is the concept of a Europe at two speeds, if not at several speeds, that prevails rather than a "new European Federation".
“We have countries in the eurozone and others outside the zone.”
“We have the Schengen area, we also have the Institute of Enhanced Cooperation.”
In the first place it was said that the countries who want it and those who do not want it will cooperate with each other.
"There will be a lot of institutes of this type and there will be a truly two-speed Europe," said Vicenova.
From this point of view, she also appreciated the mission of the Czech Republic and Herman Van Rompuye to determine the basis on which all themes having an impact on the EU should be debated among all EU members and not only the members of the eurozone.
History of a brand:
IBM innovator begins the second century of its existence
If anyone were to look for the term that best expresses IBM strategy, the closest one would be “the long-term.”
For a wide audience IBM is the symbol of the technological revolution, is a firm felt as very current and yet since its creation it has passed a hundred years.
The foundation for this long-term strategy was laid by the firm’s first leader, the visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He left this slogan that a lot of global problems can be solved as long as people are willing to think.
Its slogan "PENSE'!" became the imprint around which the life of a giant future will develop (and also the title of the internal magazine that IBM began editing in 1935).
This was the basis of Watson's culture of the healthcare company.
For us, IBM means a long-term thinking of continuous forward-looking movements.
IBM has survived a hundred years thanks to the fact that it has always remained true to its core values and yet has not been afraid to change all the others around it.
This allowed us to transform technology, business and society during our first century.
We hope that in the second century we will reach even more"delayed for the anniversary the current director of the firm Samuel J. Palmisano.
A well-prepared system
Watson, in the 1930s, started caring for his employees like Bata in the Czech Republic -- the people at IBM were the only ones among the first American employees to have paid vacation, employer-paid insurance plus a sleek employee uniform and a well-developed system of rewards for inventors and merchants.
Similarly, IBM has a well-developed customer relationship system.
The company was at the beginning brilliant in the discovery of talent--as one of the first firms to abolish all forms of discrimination and thus had a choice.
The current plan is completely in the spirit of the anti-discrimination strategy since it will be a woman - Virginia Rometty - who should replace Palmisano at the head of IBM.
She has worked at IBM for thirty years and is currently Head of Sales, Marketing and Strategy.
IBM over the past few years has been doing what is called jamy, brainstorming online, from which a lot of future strategies and innovations have emerged.
No wonder he has a lot of ideas - in the firm there are nearly 500,000 people working.
