There was no agreement as to who had the right to vote in the General Assembly - only, it seems, the statutory representatives or also the officials with full powers.
In this single point there has been a partial agreement since that time with the help of the Office for State and Law, according to which representation on the basis of full power is not possible.
Differences still persist about the rules for the election.
