"The point of disagreement lies in either proceeding according to the statutes or finding another model," said one of the three vice-presidents of the Czech Football Association, Dusan Svoboda, who represents professional football within the association.
According to the rules of the planned model, in the third round, the candidate who has received the most percentage votes in the chamber for which he is a candidate wins.
Moravia is ready, according to what is being said, to withdraw so that the candidate who has received the highest percentage of votes from both chambers wins.
And the Czech side is studying the condition that the winner should have at least two-thirds of the percentages of votes.
"Only that would then lose the idea of two previous rounds and it would completely reject the bicameral concept," admits Svoboda, who understands the objections of the Moravian side and according to which it would be best not to change the rules and vote according to the statutes in force.
