"Today's possible qualification for the European Championship should calm everyone down."
"Football will be on a wave of happiness again and there will be more enthusiasm for cooperation," adds the Jablonec officer who among the three has the greatest experience in the direction of football both professionally and at the regional level.
Rajchl is more pessimistic.
“I believe in this agreement but unfortunately the situation is very tense.”
"This is not a problem between Czechs and Moravians, but there are tendencies to want to change the drawing regulations."
"This can again cause a blockade at the General Assembly."
"I still hope that healthy reason will win," Rajchl said.
